                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>writes. Still we have a<lb/> public duty to perform to the<lb/> illustrious dead, and\n                must<lb/> not permit the Israelite to<lb/> claim fellowship with\n                Rambam<add>?</add>.<lb/> I will therefore send you<lb/> in the course of this\n                week—say<lb/> on <date>Wednesday</date> or <date>Thursday</date>—a<lb/> paper on\n                “Jewish doctrine”<lb/> “<persName>Maimonides</persName> on a future<lb/> state,\n                Repentance, and the<lb/> resurrection of the dead”<lb/> which I trust, in\n                addition<lb/> to disposing of the “Israelite” will<lb/> have the merit of a word\n                in<lb/> season for the <add>ימים הנוראים הבע\"ל</add></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I shall want a Bible<lb/> to give away. What is the<lb/> very lowest\n                price for a copy<lb/> plainly bound.?[sic]</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3736mn5v/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
